  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Substitute for y",
      "content": "Use $y=3x+9$ in the second equation.<br/>$$3(3x+9)=8x-6$$<br/>$$9x+27=8x-6$$<br/>$$x=-33$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Find y and subtract",
      "content": "Substitute $x=-33$ into $y=3x+9$.<br/>$$y=3(-33)+9=-90$$<br/>Then subtract.<br/>$$x-y=-33-(-90)=57$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Calculator shortcut",
      "content": "Graph the equations and use their intersection point. Then subtract the displayed $y$-coordinate from the displayed $x$-coordinate. The answer is <strong>D</strong>.",
